quran[15]{c,v,t}:
  50,1,"Qāf. By the Glorious Recital{1}. . .{2}",footnotes:1:The Arabic word used is Qur’anwhich literally means ‘recital’ or ‘recitation’.|2:That which is sworn is omitted so that the reader may ponder.
  50,2,"But they marveled that a forewarner had come to them from among them, so the deniers said, “How strange!"
  50,3,"Can it be that when we have died and become dust . . .{1}? This is a far-fetched return.”",footnotes:1:This sentence is left open-ended; according to Al-Alousi and other exegetes the predicate is elided but can be understood as: “. . . that we shall be brought back again?”
  50,4,"We have already known what the earth consumes of them, and with Us is a constantly preserving record{1}.",footnotes:1:Literally ‘scripture’.
  50,5,"But they rejected the truth when it came to them, so they are in a state of confusion."
  50,6,"Have they not looked at the sky above them—how We constructed it and decoratedit and how it has no fractures?"
  50,7,"And the earth—how We spread it out and set on it firm mountains and germinated therein all kinds of lovely plants,"
  50,8,"an eye-opener and a reminder for every penitent servant?"
  50,9,"And We brought down from the sky blessed water and germinated with it gardens and grain to harvest,"
  50,10,"and the soaring palm trees with clustered dates—"
  50,11,"provision for the servants. And We revived thereby a lifeless land; likewise is the emergence."
  50,12,"Before them the people of Noah disbelieved, and<i class=""s"">(so did) </i>the fellows of Al-Russ and Thamûd"
  50,13,"and ʻĀd and Pharaoh and the brethren of Lot"
  50,14,"and the fellows of the Thicket and the people of Tubbaʻ; they all disbelieved the messengers, so My threat came true."
  50,15,"Were We fatigued by the first creation? Rather, they are in doubt of a new creation."
